     The left-continuous unit step function; thus `unit_step (<x>)'
     vanishes for `<x> <= 0' and equals 1 for `<x> > 0'.

     If you want a unit step function that takes on the value 1/2 at
     zero, use `(1 + signum (<x>))/2'.


